NNMF uses the algorithm by Lee and Seung33, which factors the p-by-n matrix E into non-negative factors W (p-by-s) and C (s-by-n) and minimizes the root mean squared residual D between E and its approximation W * C, starting from random initial values W0 and C0. This procedure is provided by the MATLAB function nnmf.m34 and is given as:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
